	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Actually, a simple flick-screen platformer with few moving objects per location (like 5) should be doable with C on NES. Main problem would be memory, not speed. At least it was made for C16 and Plus/4, a simple homebrew platformer Uwol by MojonTwins <a href="http://translate.google.com/translate?js=n&amp;prev=_t&amp;hl=ru&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;layout=2&amp;eotf=1&amp;sl=es&amp;tl=en&amp;u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mojontwins.com%2F2010%2F10%2F15%2Fuwol-quest-for-money-para-c16-y-plus4-por-kichy%2F" class="postlink">was ported there</a>, originally it was written in C for ZX Spectrum, and then ported (using the original source code) by fans to few other platforms. A slow paced non-action game like Dizzy is doable for sure.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


