	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The NES has plenty of read-only memory, of course.  Looking at those specs it sounds like only the 'dynamic memory' needs to be RAM.  The "small game" example shows over a little over 2kB in dynamic memory.  By adding a WRAM to the cart, it theoretically should fit that example.

		

		</td>
